ket%20%26quot%3Bnon-fraternisation%26quot%3B%20policy%20has%20been%20unheard%20of%20since%20the%20Cold-War%2C%20since%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20American%20diplomats%20in%20other%20countries%20to%20date%20locals%20or%20marry%20them.%20Until%20the%20new%20ban%20in%20January%2C%20US%20personnel%20in%20China%20were%20expected%20to%20inform%20their%20seniors%20about%20any%20intimate%20contact%20with%20Chinese%20citizens%2C%20but%20were%20not%20explicitly%20forbidden%20from%20sexual%20or%20romantic%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20policy%20is%20a%20response%20to%20concerns%20over%20potential%20security%20risks%2C%20particularly%20in%20light%20of%20China's%20alleged%20use%20of%20%26quot%3Bhoneypots%26quot%3B%20to%20extract%20sensitive%20information%20from%20American%20diplomats.%20According%20to%20Peter%20Mattis%2C%20a%20former%20CIA%20analyst%2C%20Chinese%20state%20security%20agents%20have%20been%20known%20to%20seduce%20American%20diplomats%2C%20and%20even%20ordinary%20Chinese%20citizens%20who%20date%20American%20diplomats%20could%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20coercion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20policy%20applies%20to%20U.S.%20personnel%20stationed%20in%20mainland%20China%2C%20including%20the%20embassy%20in%20Beijing%20and%20consulates%20in%20Guangzhou%2C%20Shanghai%2C%20Shenyang%2C%20and%20Wuhan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20American%20consulate%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%20However%2C%20it%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20U.S.%20personnel%20stationed%20outside%20China.%20Those%20with%20pre-existing%20relationships%20with%20Chinese%20citizens%20can%20apply%20for%20exemptions%2C%20but%20if%20denied%2C%20they%20must%20end%20the%20relationship%20or%20leave%20their%20position.%20If%20the%20policy%20is%20violated%2C%20the%20concerned%20personnel%20would%20be%20ordered%20to%20leave%20China%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20policy%20marks%20a%20significant%20shift%20in%20the%20U.S.%20government's%20approach%20to%20security%20in%20China%2C%20reflecting%20growing%20tensions%20between%20Washington%20and%20Beijing%20over%20trade%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20geopolitical%20competition.%20The%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20has%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20policy%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bmore%20appropriate%20to%20ask%20the%20U.S.%20about%20this%20question.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20China%20has%20its%20own%20set%20of%20strict%20regulations%20governing%20the%20personal%20lives%20of%20its%20personnel%20overseas.%20Chinese%20civil%20servants%20with%20spouses%20who%20have%20acquired%20foreign%20citizenship%20are%20barred%20from%20promotions%2C%20and%20diplomats%20are%20restricted%20from%20spending%20extended%20periods%20in%20one%20country.%20Additionally%2C%20Chinese%20officials%20and%20staff%20are%20prohibited%20from%20engaging%20in%20romantic%20or%20sexual%20relationships%20with%20foreign%20citizens.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743682380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-06%2Fvhqfpq0o_donald-trump-xi-jinping-reuters_625x300_29_June_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-the-us-has-banned-diplomats-from-romantic-sexual-relations-with-chinese-8078314%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20policy%20is%20a%20response%20to%20concerns%20over%20potential%20security%20risks%2C%20particularly%20in%20light%20of%20China's%20alleged%20use%20of%20%26quot%3Bhoneypots%26quot%3B%20to%20extract%20sensitive%20information%20from%20American%20diplomats.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-the-us-has-banned-diplomats-from-romantic-sexual-relations-with-chinese-8078314%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Kangana%20stuck%20to%20Ranbir%20is%20a%20'serial%20skirt%20chaser'%20remark%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743682352000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fpho