%20with%20Newark%20in%20the%20US%20and%20had%20their%20photos%20taken%20with%20many%20leaders%20across%20the%20globe.%20But%20their%20luck%20may%20have%20finally%20run%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20the%20South%20American%20country%20of%20Bolivia%20said%20last%20week%20that%20they%20have%20arrested%2020%20people%20linked%20to%20'Kailasa'%20after%20they%20signed%201%2C000-year%20leases%20with%20indigenous%20groups%20in%20the%20country%20for%20vast%20tracts%20of%20the%20Amazon%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agreements%20were%20nullified%20and%20the%20representatives%20of%20the%20fake%20country%20were%20deported%20to%20the%20real%20nations%20they%20belonged%20to%2C%20including%20India%2C%20the%20US%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBolivia%20does%20not%20maintain%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20the%20alleged%20nation%20'United%20States%20of%20Kailasa%2C'%26quot%3B%20Bolivia's%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F04%2F03%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Funited-states-of-kailasa-bolivia.html%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20of%20'Kailasa'%20had%20managed%20to%20get%20a%20photo%20taken%20with%20the%20president%20of%20Bolivia%2C%20Luis%20Arce%20and%20Bolivian%20newspaper%20El%20Deber%20said%20leases%20had%20been%20signed%20with%20indigenous%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPedro%20Guasico%2C%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20Baure%2C%20one%20of%20the%20indigenous%20groups%2C%20said%20its%20contact%20with%20'Kailasa'%20representatives%20had%20begun%20in%20late%202024%2C%20after%20they%20offered%20help%20with%20forest%20fires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20then%20negotiated%20a%20lease%20for%20land%20%26quot%3Bthree%20times%20the%20size%20of%20New%20Delhi%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20Baure%20agreed%20to%20a%2025-year%20deal%20which%20would%20net%20them%20nearly%20%24200%2C000%20annually.%20The%20'Kailasa'%20representatives'%20draft%2C%20though%2C%20was%20for%20a%20lease%20of%201%2C000%20years%20and%20included%20the%20use%20of%20airspace%20and%20extraction%20of%20natural%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Baure%20signed%20the%20lease.%20%26quot%3BWe%20made%20the%20mistake%20of%20listening%20to%20them.%20They%20offered%20us%20that%20money%20as%20an%20annual%20bonus%20for%20conserving%20and%20protecting%20our%20territory%2C%20but%20it%20was%20completely%20false%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Guasico%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20the%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20'Country'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENithyananda%20had%20a%20large%20following%20in%20India%20before%20he%20was%20arrested%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20sex%20scandal%20in%202010.%20Reports%20had%20said%20that%20after%20fleeing%20India%20in%202019%20following%20sexual%20assault%20allegations%2C%20he%20had%20bought%20an%20island%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Ecuador%2C%20another%20South%20American%20country.%20'Kailasa'%2C%20Nithyananda%20and%20his%20followers%20announced%20on%20YouTube%2C%20was%20dedicated%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bpreservation%2C%20restoration%20and%20revival%20of%20an%20enlightened%20culture%20and%20civilisation%20based%20on%20authentic%20Hinduism%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENithyananda%20had%20said%20that%20his%20new%20status%20as%20the%20head%20of%20a%20state%20granted%20him%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20representatives%20of%20'Kailasa'%20had%20attended%20a%20United%20Nations%20meeting%20and%20demanded%20protection%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bsupreme%20pontiff%20of%20Hinduism%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20of%20United%20Nations%20Committee%20on%20Economic%2C%20Social%20and%20Cultural%20Rights%20(CESCR)%20was%20held%20in%20Geneva%20and%20videos%20showed%20one%20of%20the%20representatives%20-%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20saree%20wearing%20a%20turban%20-%20extolling%20the%20sustainable%20development%20initiatives%20taken%20by%20her%20'country'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20claimed%20Nithyananda%20has%20been%20targeted%20for%20reviving%20the%20ancient%20traditions%20of%20Hinduism%20and%20was%20banned%20from%20his%20birth%20country%20and%20asked%20the%20UN%20body%20what%20measures%20can%20be%20taken%20''at%20national%20and%20international%20levels''%20to%20stop%20his%20persecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuotable%20quotes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENithyananda%20is%20known%20for%20his%20quotable%20quotes%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20shared%20widely%20and%20often%20mocked%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20the%20me%20resides%20in%20this%20as%20me%20is%20residing%20in%20all%20of%20that%20as%20me%20so%20that%20me%20through%20this%20me%20talking%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20self-styled%20godman%20had%20famously%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20going%20to%20be%20active%2C%20healthy%20at%20least%20for%20the%20next%20150%20years.%20The%20Hindu%20enemies%20and%20Hindu%20traitors%20wasted%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20time%20and%20I%20don't%20go%20and%20attack%20them%20or%20react%20to%20them...%20I%20just%20decide%20to%20live%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743681780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2F7n096tr8_nithyananda-kailasa-gold-650_625x300_03_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnithyananda-republic-of-kailasa-united-states-of-kailasa-godman-he-founded-hindu-nation-then-attempted-to-take-over-land-in-bolivia-8078337%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nithyananda%20fled%20India%20in%202019%2C%20leaving%20behind%20a%20sprawling%20religious%20empire%2C%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20child%20abduction%2C%20sexual%20assault%20and%20abuse%2C%20and%20claimed%20to%20have%20founded%20the%20nation%20of%20'Kailasa'%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20haven%26quot%3B%20for%20Hindus.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canon