Url%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22EU%20Council%20President%20urges%20faster%20trade%20deals%20with%20India%20amid%20US%20tariffs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743680954000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Feu-trade-deals-india-us-tariffs-costa-125040301004_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22European%20Council%20President%20Antonio%20Costa%20voiced%20full%20support%20for%20the%20EU%20Commission's%20ongoing%20trade%20negotiations%20with%20the%20US%20and%20highlighted%20the%20role%20of%20trade%20in%20global%20prosperity%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Trump%20Just%20Changed%20The%20Very%20Meaning%20Of%20Tariffs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20fellow%20Americans%2C%20this%20is%20Liberation%20Day%2C%20waiting%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20April%202%2C%202025%2C%20will%20forever%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20day%20American%20industry%20was%20reborn%2C%20the%20day%20America's%20destiny%20was%20reclaimed%20and%20the%20day%20that%20we%20began%20to%20make%20America%20wealthy%20again.%26quot%3B%20These%20were%20the%20words%20of%20American%20President%20Donald%20J.%20Trump%20as%20he%20announced%20a%20string%20of%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20for%20countries%2C%20shaking%20up%20the%20global%20trade%20framework.%20The%20tariffs%2C%20he%20said%2C%20were%20in%20response%20to%20longstanding%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20by%20both%20friendly%20and%20unfriendly%20nations%20alike.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%20of%20America's%20'Liberation%20Day'%20are%20only%20just%20starting%20to%20be%20seen.%20Markets%20in%20Asia%20are%20already%20tumbling.%20Gold%20prices%20have%20surged%20to%20a%20record%20high%2C%20approaching%20%243%2C200%2Foz%20as%20investors%20rush%20to%20hedge%20against%20economic%20uncertainty.%20%C2%A0The%20US%20President's%20weaponisation%20of%20tariff%20regulations%20to%20reorient%20production%2C%20investment%20and%20distributive%20supply%20chains%20can%20end%20up%20overhauling%20trade%20relations%20between%20nations%20across%20regions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Tough%20Road%20For%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20respect%20to%20India%2C%20the%20newly%20imposed%2026%25%20duty%20on%20exports%20is%20likely%20to%20disrupt%20trade%20and%20rattle%20financial%20markets%20in%20both%20countries%20in%20the%20short%20to%20medium%20term.%20A%20recent%20report%20estimated%20that%20if%20the%20US%20imposed%20a%20broad%20country-level%20tariff%20of%2025%25%20on%20Indian%20imports%2C%20India's%20GDP%20could%20take%20a%20%2431-billion%20hit.%20This%20figure%20may%20be%20much%20higher%20now%2C%20given%20the%20indirect%20impact%20of%20tariffs%20on%20countries%20where%20American%20and%20Indian%20product%20supply%20chains%20are%20deeply%20interconnected.%20It%20will%20also%20cause%20prices%20of%20inputs%20and%20intermediate%20goods%20to%20rise%2C%20which%20will%20add%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20production.%20The%20most%20affected%20sectors%20in%20the%20Indo-American%20context%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20electronics%2C%20gems%20and%20jewelry%20and%20pharmaceuticals.%20All%20of%20this%20forms%20a%20crucial%20backbone%20of%20India's%20rapidly%20growing%20export%20economy%3A%20in%20the%20case%20of%20smartphones%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20India%20contributes%20around%2010%25%20of%20US%20imports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20measures%20also%20include%20a%20universal%20baseline%2025%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20automobiles%3B%20India%20will%20be%20subjected%20to%20this%20too%2C%20regardless%20of%20any%20potential%20exemptions%20granted%20to%20it.%20Indian%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20which%20account%20for%20%247%20billion%20in%20exports%20to%20the%20US%20and%20contribute%20to%20about%2047%25%20of%20America's%20generic%20drugs%2C%20will%20see%20raised%20costs.%20Similarly%2C%20India's%20%249%20billion%20textile%20sector%2C%20which%20is%20again%20a%20labour-intensive%20industry%2C%20will%20struggle%20against%20cheaper%20competitors%20like%20Vietnam%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20risking%20millions%20of%20jobs.%20The%20%248.58%20billion%20jewellery%20export%20industry%20will%20lose%20its%20price%20advantage%20to%20rivals%20such%20as%20China%20and%20Belgium.%20Auto%20parts%20exports%2C%20valued%20at%20%242%20billion%2C%20will%20face%20setbacks%2C%20which%20will%20disrupt%20supply%20chains%20for%20US%20manufacturers.%20Even%20IT%20services%2C%20which%20send%20almost%20%24100%20billion%20in%20exports%20to%20the%20US%2C%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20retaliatory%20measures%20that%20could%20destabilise%20India's%20largest%20foreign%20exchange%20earner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETariffs%20Are%20Not%20New%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20specific%20details%20about%20the%20implementation%20of%20these%20tariffs%20remain%20unclear%2C%20the%20broader%20picture%20reveals%20Trump's%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20protectionist%20policies.%20But%20is%20that%20approach%20new%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20before%20Trump's%20current%20theatrics%20on%20tariffs%2C%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20own%20trade%20policy%20had%20increased%20the%20size%20and%20scope%20of%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration's%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20imports.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20combination%20of%20tariffs%20and%20industrial%20policies%20to%20boost%20demand%20for%20American%20domestic%20goods%20and%20incentivise%20investment%20delivered%20the%20manufacturing%20boom%20that%20Trump%20keeps%20promising.%20It's%20important%20to%20note%20how%20by%202023%2C%20the%20United%20States%20had%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20investment%20in%20factories%20in%2030%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Lori%20Wallach%20recently%20argued%2C%20%26quot%3BLabeling%20tariffs%20as%20merely%20Trumpian%20is%20a%20mistake%20that%20Trump's%20critics%20have%20repeatedly%20made%20in%20and%20outside%20the%20US%26quot%3B.%20If%20you%20support%20a%20carbon%20border%20tax%20to%20combat%20climate%20change%2C%20or%20enforcement%20of%20labour%20standards%20in%20trade%20pacts%2C%20you%20support%20tariffs.%20And%20tariffs%20are%2C%20mostly%2C%20popular%E2%80%94even%20if%20not%20practical.%20%E2%80%9CShortly%20before%20the%20US%20presidential%20election%2C%2056%25%20of%20Americans%20favored%20increasing%20tariffs%2C%20with%20support%20among%20non-college-educated%20voters%20in%20Michigan%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20and%20Ohio%20at%2058%25%E2%80%9D%2C%20wrote%20Wallach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlashbacks%20From%20Trump's%20First%20Term%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Trump%20did%20in%20his%20first%20term%20was%20reframe%20tariffs%20not%20as%20economic%20tools%20but%20as%20instruments%20of%20national%20revival%2C%20something%20that%20allowed%20him%20to%20renegotiate%20trade%20deals%20to%20work%20in%20American%20interests.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20he%20is%20simply%20continuing%20now%20what%20he%20started%20then%2C%20but%20to%20a%20much%20intense%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20views%20trade%20deficits%20not%20as%20economic%20imbalances%20but%20as%20evidence%20of%20foreign%20exploitation.%20The%20measures%20launched%20by%20him%20in%202018%20included%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20and%2010%25%20on%20aluminum%20imports%20from%20multiple%20countries%2C%20including%20allies%20like%20Canada%20and%20the%20European%20Union.%20The%20centerpiece%20of%20this%20trade%20war%2C%20however%2C%20was%20China.%20By%20imposing%20tariffs%20on%20over%20Chinese%20goods%20worth%20%24370%20billion%2C%20the%20administration%20ignited%20a%20tit-for-tat%20trade%20war%20that%20came%20to%20reshape%20US-China%20relations.%20The%20tensions%20evidently%20culminated%20in%20the%202020%20%E2%80%9CPhase%20One%E2%80%9D%20deal%20with%20China%2C%20which%20failed%20to%20meet%20its%20lofty%20purchase%20targets%20and%20left%20most%20tariffs%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20previous%20administrations%20that%20focused%20on%20liberalisation%20and%20multilateral%20engagement%2C%20Trump%20treated%20trade%20as%20a%20zero-sum%20game.%20His%20logic%20was%20simple%3A%20if%20the%20US%20runs%20a%20deficit%20with%20another%20country%2C%20tariffs%20would%20be%20imposed.%20In%20his%20last%20term%2C%20he%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Trans-Pacific%20Partnership%20(TPP)%20on%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office%20and%20pushed%20for%20the%20renegotiation%20of%20NAFTA%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20United%20States-Mexico-Canada%20Agreement%20(USMCA)%2C%20a%20pact%20that%20demonstrated%20his%20preference%20for%20bilateral%20renegotiation%20over%20multilateral%20cooperation.%20The%20step%20was%20much%20more%20symbolic%20than%20radical.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsequences%2C%20Consequences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETariff%20wars%2C%20however%2C%20are%20costly%2C%20even%20if%20populist%20fervour%20may%20make%20people%20lose%20sight%20of%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20economic%20studies%2C%20including%20one%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%2C%20have%20shown%20how%20tariffs%20disproportionately%20affected%20American%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20in%20the%20past.%20In%20Trump's%20last%20term%2C%20the%20prices%20of%20retail%20and%20consumer%20goods%20skyrocketed%2C%20while%20importers%20struggled%20with%20uncertainty%20and%20shifting%20supply%20chains%2C%20with%20some%20relocating%20production%20to%20Mexico%20or%20Vietnam.%20Although%20this%20began%20as%20a%20battle%20over%20trade%20balances%2C%20it%20rapidly%20evolved%20into%20strategic%20decoupling%2C%20something%20that%20only%20became%20more%20layered%20and%20deterrent%20with%20time.%20US%20farmers%20faced%20collateral%20damage%20as%20China's%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20devastated%20soybean%20exports%2C%20forcing%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20provide%20over%20%2428%20billion%20in%20subsidies.%20Farm%20bankruptcies%20spiked%20in%20several%20Midwestern%20states%2C%20though%20Trump%20did%20manage%20to%20retain%20strong%20rural%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20overall%20US%20trade%20deficit%20widened%20during%20Trump's%20last%20term%2C%20and%20the%20trade%20deficit%20with%20China%2C%20while%20temporarily%20shrinking%2C%20eventually%20rebounded%2C%20highlighting%20the%20limitations%20of%20tariffs%20as%20a%20long-term%20corrective%20measure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%E2%80%94once%20a%20major%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20US%20Generalized%20System%20of%20Preferences%20(GSP)%E2%80%94the%202019%20US%20decision%20to%20revoke%20its%20special%20status%20eliminated%20duty-free%20access%20for%20over%20%246%20billion%20worth%20of%20Indian%20exports%2C%20particularly%20hurting%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20enterprises%20(SMEs)%20in%20sectors%20like%20textiles%2C%20auto%20parts%2C%20and%20leather.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMultilateralism%20To%20Bilateralism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20US%20administrations%20in%20the%20past%20pursued%20global%20trade%20liberalisation%20through%20multilateral%20agreements.%20The%20Obama%20administration%20negotiated%20the%20TPP%2C%20a%20sweeping%20pact%20aimed%20at%20countering%20China's%20influence%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20alongside%20reducing%20tariffs%20among%2012%20Pacific%20Rim%20nations.%20However%2C%20opposition%20from%20both%20left%20and%20right%20killed%20US%20participation%20before%20ratification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Trump's%20approach%20represented%20a%20paradigm%20shift%3A%20from%20multilateralism%20to%20bilateralism%2C%20from%20trade%20liberalisation%20to%20trade%20confrontation.%20And%2C%20Joe%20Biden's%20decision%20not%20to%20dismantle%20Trump's%20tariffs%20only%20reflected%20the%20political%20popularity%20of%20protectionism%2C%20even%20though%20the%20strategy%20was%20different.%20Biden%20emphasised%20reengagement%20with%20allies%2C%20modernisation%20of%20trade%20tools%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98friend-shoring'%2C%20encouraging%20US-based%20companies%20to%20move%20production%20to%20trusted%20allies%20rather%20than%20adversaries%20like%20China.%20He%20also%20approached%20protectionism%20in%20a%20different%20way%3A%20through%20%E2%80%98strategic%20investment'.%20For%20instance%2C%20his%20administration%20passed%20the%20CHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act%20(2022)%20to%20boost%20domestic%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%20and%20reduce%20dependence%20on%20China%2C%20Taiwan%20and%20South%20Korea.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20(IRA)%20was%20passed%20to%20support%20clean%20energy%20and%20reduce%20dependency%20on%20Chinese%20materials%20by%20conditioning%20subsidies%20on%20domestic%20production.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20Productivism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20all%20this%20signals%20is%20an%20American%20turn%20towards%20economic%20productivism%2C%20that%20is%2C%20a%20set%20of%20policies%20that%20enable%20a%20rise%20in%20productivity%20and%20%E2%80%98good'%2C%20secured%20jobs%20if%20pursued%20through%20a%20renegotiated%20trade%20policy.%20To%20what%20extent%20Trump%20can%20achieve%20this%20in%20his%20second%20term%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20but%20there%20is%20precedent.%20Ronald%20Reagan%20pursued%20similar%20trade%20tactics%20against%20Japan%20(in%20reducing%20automobile%20imports%20from%20Japan%20to%20America%20using%20Quotas)%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Japanese%20cars%20were%20ruling%20the%20international%20market.%20His%20actions%20substantively%20brought%20Japanese%20automobile%20investments%20into%20the%20US%2C%20shaping%20the%20industry%20in%20the%20southern%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20have%20used%20tariffs%20to%20cater%20to%20domestic%20constituencies%2C%20proving%20how%20deeply%20embedded%20they%20are%20in%20electoral%20strategies.%20Trump's%20%E2%80%98America%20First'%20policy%2C%20specifically%20targeting%20the%20Rust%20Belt%20where%20trade%20with%20China%20and%20globalisation%20had%20long%20been%20held%20responsible%20for%20the%20manufacturing%20collapse%2C%20was%20what%20got%20him%20into%20office%20for%20a%20second%20time%E2%80%94against%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20whose%20stand%20on%20tariffs%20ended%20up%20costing%20Democrats%20a%20large%20section%20of%20working-class%20votes.%20Blue-collar%20workers%20continued%20to%20support%20his%20protectionist%20stance%2C%20disregarding%20evidence%20that%20retaliatory%20actions%20had%20adversely%20affected%20their%20economic%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtectionism%2C%20thus%2C%20is%20no%20longer%20limited%20to%20right-wing%20populism%20today%2C%20but%20woven%20into%20mainstream%20bipartisan%20politics.%20In%20an%20era%20of%20fractured%20alliances%2C%20tariffs%20have%20(unfortunately)%20become%20signals%20of%20distrust%2C%20punishment%2C%20and%20alignment%E2%80%94tools%20not%20just%20of%20economics%20but%20of%20power%20projection%20in%20a%20multipolar%20and%20multi-fragmented%20world%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Deepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Dean%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Visiting%20Research%20Fellow%20at%20Department%20of%20Asian%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies%20(AMES)%2C%20University%20of%20Oxford.%C2%A0Ankur%20Singh%20and%20Aditi%20Desai%20contributed%20to%20the%20piece.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743680940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F2p0p15b_donald-trump_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-blame-trump-alone-when-even-biden-loved-tariffs-8076876%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Both%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20have%20used%20tariffs%20to%20cater%20to%20domestic%20constituencies%2C%20provi