o%20a%20report%20by%20The%20Washington%20Post.%20The%20report%20said%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20end%20automatic%20citizenship%20for%20those%20born%20in%20the%20US%20are%20also%20making%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%20fear%20that%20their%20future%20children%20could%20be%20stateless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20H-1B%20visa%20programme%20allows%20US%20employers%20to%20hire%20foreign%20workers%20in%20so-called%20specialty%20occupations.%20Every%20year%2C%2065%2C000%20such%20visas%20are%20issued%20through%20a%20lottery%20system.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20Indians%20have%20received%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20H-1B%20visas%2C%20followed%20by%20Chinese%20and%20Canadian%20nationals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETech%20Industry's%20Reliance%20on%20Immigrants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESilicon%20Valley's%20immigrant%20tech%20community%20has%20long%20been%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20key%20forces%20behind%20the%20US%20competitiveness%20in%20the%20technology%20sector.%20According%20to%20a%202018%20study%20by%20think%20tank%20National%20Foundation%20for%20American%20Policy%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20US%20start-ups%20valued%20at%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20had%20an%20immigrant%20founder%20or%20co-founder.%20The%20executives%20of%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20tech%20giants%20in%20the%20US%20are%20immigrants%2C%20including%20those%20of%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20Uber%20and%20chip%20giant%20Nvidia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20under%20Trump's%20immigration%20policies%2C%20the%20future%20of%20this%20community%20in%20the%20country%20is%20uncertain.%20Experts%20believe%20that%20reducing%20the%20immigrant%20workforce%20from%20the%20tech%20industry%20could%20hamper%20America's%20ability%20to%20compete%20with%20China%20in%20the%20race%20to%20develop%20sophisticated%20technology%20like%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20we're%20seeing%20right%20now%20is%20just%20a%20lot%20of%20worry%20and%20panic...It%20seems%20like%20%5Bthe%20administration%20is%5D%20just%20getting%20more%20and%20more%20momentum%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20know%20what's%20around%20the%20corner%2C%E2%80%9D%20Malcolm%20Goeschl%2C%20principal%20attorney%20for%20Goeschl%20Law%2C%20a%20San%20Francisco-based%20firm%20focused%20on%20business%20immigration%20that%20serves%20clients%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20Amazon%20had%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20H-1B%20visas%20approved%20amongst%20all%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20in%20America%2C%20followed%20by%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20Microsoft%20and%20Apple.%20Tesla%2C%20whose%20billionaire%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%20is%20a%20close%20aide%20of%20President%20Trump%20and%20is%20leading%20the%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20cut%20federal%20spending%2C%20had%201%2C767%20approved%20H1Bs%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20ending%20in%20September%202024.%20IT%20outsourcing%20companies%20like%20Infosys%20and%20Cognizant%20also%20account%20for%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20H1B%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EH-1B%20Workers%20Worried%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20late%20last%20year%2C%20before%20Trump%20took%20the%20oath%20of%20office%2C%20law%20firms%20working%20for%20Google%20and%20Amazon%20warned%20the%20companies'%20employees%20with%20visas%20to%20think%20twice%20before%20traveling%20abroad%2C%20out%20of%20concern%20they%20might%20not%20be%20allowed%20back%20into%20the%20U.S%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20two%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%20told%20the%20publication%20that%20they%20had%20to%20cancel%20their%20travel%20plans%20to%20India%20amid%20fear%20of%20being%20denied%20re-entry%20to%20the%20US.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20Indian%20immigrant%20said%20his%20elder%20daughter%20was%20born%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20but%20the%20future%20of%20his%20second%20child%20seems%20opaque%20as%20they%20may%20not%20get%20citizenship%20in%20either%20the%20US%20or%20India.%20%E2%80%9CThere's%20an%20assumption%20that%20everybody%20who%20is%20not%20a%20US%20citizen%20might%20be%20here%20illegally%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20told%20the%20publication%20through%20an%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertainty%20has%20also%20created%20some%20practical%20challenges%2C%20as%20many%20immigrants%20are%20always%20carrying%20their%20documentation%20while%20in%20public.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we're%20walking%20around%2C%20we%20always%20carry%20our%20documents%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20other%20worker%20said%20through%20her%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20lawyers%20are%20also%20reporting%20anxieties%20among%20immigrants%20due%20to%20worries%20over%20unexpected%20changes%20to%20visa%20processes%2C%20which%20are%20negatively%20affecting%20their%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20definitely%20impacts%20their%20performance%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20HR%20representative%20of%20a%20tech%20firm%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2025%2F03%2F31%2Fimmigration-h1b-fear-siliconvalley%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20threat%20is%20looming%20that%20some%20action%20will%20be%20taken%20against%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HR%20representative%20added%20that%20the%20uncertainty%20is%20also%20adding%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20company%2C%20as%20they%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20expediting%20the%20processing%20of%20some%20H-1B%20extensions%20to%20counteract%20delays%20related.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUncertainty%20Over%20Visa%20and%20Green%20Cards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20H1B%20visas%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20bone%20of%20contention%20among%20Trump's%20supporters.%20This%20was%20visible%20in%20December%20when%20the%20two%20sides%20argued%20on%20X%20over%20whether%20Trump%20should%20boost%20or%20suppress%20skilled%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20super%20talented%20engineers%20AND%20super%20motivated%20in%20the%20USA%20is%20far%20too%20low...%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20want%20your%20TEAM%20to%20win%20the%20championship%2C%20you%20need%20to%20recruit%20top%20talent%20wherever%20they%20may%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20Elon%20Musk%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20Christmas.%20He%20received%20pushback%20from%20some%20Republicans%2C%20including%20former%20presidential%20hopeful%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20who%20said%20the%20country%20should%20invest%20in%20education%20to%20train%20more%20American-born%20tech%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Trump%20has%20not%20said%20anything%20about%20ending%20the%20H1B%20program%20or%20other%20skilled%20visas%3B%20however%2C%20it%20was%20part%20of%20his%20agenda%20in%20his%20first%20term.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnMeanwhile%2C%20the%20processing%20of%20Green%20Card%20requests%2C%20which%20is%20immigrants'%20path%20to%20permanent%20residency%2C%20is%20also%20facing%20unprecedented%20delays.%20Even%20Aravind%20Srinivas%2C%20CEO%20of%20AI%20company%20Perplexity%2C%20that%20recently%20valued%20at%20%249%20billion%2C%20said%20on%20social%20media%20that%20he%20has%20been%20waiting%20three%20years%20for%20a%20green%20card%20despite%20founding%20a%20company%20that%20employs%20hundreds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20mostly%20have%20no%20idea%20when%20they%20talk%20about%20immigration%2C%E2%80%9D%20Srinivas%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743667740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fk0066ec8_google-reuters_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-big-techs-like-google-amazon-warned-h-1b-visa-holders-to-not-leave-us-8076460%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thousands%20of%20immigrant%20techies%2C%20including%20Indians%2C%20are%20living%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%20uncertainty%20over%